---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
const baseUrl = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, "");
---

<Base title="Scope of Business Exposure">
  <p class="back-link">
    <a href={baseUrl || "/"}>← Back to landscape</a>
  </p>

  <header class="about-hero" style="--accent:#5fae5f">
    <span class="hero-icon" aria-hidden="true">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
        <ellipse cx="12" cy="5" rx="8" ry="3" />
        <path d="M4 5 V12 C4 14.5 8 15.5 12 15.5 C16 15.5 20 14.5 20 12 V5" />
        <path d="M4 12 V19 C4 21.5 8 22.5 12 22.5 C16 22.5 20 21.5 20 19 V12" />
      </svg>
    </span>
    <h1>Scope of Business Exposure</h1>
    <p class="hero-tag">The X axis: from narrowly technical to organisation-wide.</p>
  </header>

  <article class="about-body">
    <p>
      Security isn't a single department. A vulnerability in a container
      image and a regulator's compliance question both demand security
      attention — but they live in completely different worlds. The X axis
      arranges security work from narrowly technical on the left to broadly
      organisational on the right.
    </p>

    <h2>Three layers, six departments</h2>

    <h3 style="color:#5b8def">Technical Security <span class="muted">(left)</span></h3>
    <p>
      Closest to the code and the infrastructure.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Infrastructure &amp; Cloud Security</strong> — networks, identities, cloud configurations.</li>
      <li><strong>AppSec &amp; Product Security</strong> — application code, dependencies, secure SDLC.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 style="color:#5fae5f">Process &amp; System Security <span class="muted">(middle)</span></h3>
    <p>
      Where signals are turned into decisions and where security engineering
      lives.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Security Engineering &amp; Data Security</strong> — DLP, data flows, security tooling.</li>
      <li><strong>Security Operations (SOC &amp; IR)</strong> — detection, alerting, incident response.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 style="color:#f1a983">Organizational Security <span class="muted">(right)</span></h3>
    <p>
      The human and governance layer of security.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>GRC &amp; TPRM</strong> — governance, risk, compliance, vendor risk management.</li>
      <li><strong>Business Resilience &amp; Security Awareness</strong> — crisis response, awareness, human risk.</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="callout">
      <strong>Why this matters:</strong> a use case sitting on the right
      touches more stakeholders and faces more organisational friction than
      one on the left. The X axis is a rough proxy for change-management
      effort.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .back-link {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .about-hero {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    text-align: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    padding: 2rem 1rem 1.5rem;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 10%, var(--bg-elevated));
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-top: 4px solid var(--accent);
    border-radius: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .hero-icon {
    width: 56px;
    height: 56px;
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .hero-icon svg {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
  }

  .about-hero h1 {
    margin: 0.25rem 0 0;
    font-size: 1.8rem;
  }

  .hero-tag {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    max-width: 50ch;
  }

  .about-body {
    max-width: 70ch;
    margin: 0 auto;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .about-body h2 {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
  }

  .about-body h3 {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .about-body ul {
    margin: 0.4rem 0 0.8rem;
    padding-left: 1.4rem;
  }

  .muted {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 0.88em;
  }

  .callout {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
    background: var(--bg-elevated);
    border-left: 3px solid #5fae5f;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
</style>
